<subSubSection id="DCDD655923764A32FF62A8743CF7E076" pageId="3" pageNumber="252" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="947836D223764A32FF62A8743E73E256" blockId="3.[136,789,1080,1840]" pageId="3" pageNumber="252">
<emphasis id="A6B3EAC023764A32FF62A8743D8BE316" box="[174,237,1081,1104]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="252">Notes.</emphasis>
− Most African 
<taxonomicName id="53C74D5123764A32FE6EA8743F5FE316" box="[418,569,1080,1104]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Tragia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="252" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="A6B3EAC023764A32FE6EA8743C8EE316" box="[418,488,1081,1104]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="252">Tragia</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
have irritating hairs in leaves, twigs and/or inflorescence. This character, that is usually very conspicuous, was not noted in the field for the 
<specimenCount id="82C1FD5B23764A32FD27A8343D92E3F6" pageId="3" pageNumber="252" type="generic">two specimens</specimenCount>
of the new species. Stinging hairs are, according to 
<bibRefCitation id="F0564B2323764A32FF44A8F53C2FE396" author="KEAY, R. W. J." box="[136,329,1208,1232]" pageId="3" pageNumber="252" pagination="364 - 423" refId="ref1954" refString="KEAY, R. W. J. (1958). Euphorbiaceae. In: KEAY, R. W. J. (ed.), Fl. W. Trop. Africa ed. 2, 1: 364 - 423." type="journal article" year="1958">KEAY (1958: 411)</bibRefCitation>
, absent in 
<emphasis id="A6B3EAC023764A32FE72A8F43F4DE396" box="[446,555,1209,1232]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="252">
<taxonomicName id="53C74D5123764A32FE72A8F43F41E396" box="[446,551,1209,1232]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Tragia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="252" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="preussii">T. preussii</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
another species from wet evergreen forest. It is not clear if the stinging hairs are really absent or maybe too small to have an effect on the human skin.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="947836D223764A32FF62A9553CF7E076" blockId="3.[136,789,1080,1840]" pageId="3" pageNumber="252">
All herbarium specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="53C74D5123764A32FE00A9543F69E276" box="[460,527,1305,1328]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Tragia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="252" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="A6B3EAC023764A32FE00A9543F69E276" box="[460,527,1305,1328]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="252">Tragia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry id="ECD0764223764A32FD80A9553FF0E276" box="[588,662,1304,1328]" name="Liberia" pageId="3" pageNumber="252">Liberia</collectingCountry>
are mapped here (
<figureCitation id="0CFC2A5723764A32FF0DA9753D9BE216" box="[193,253,1336,1360]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[136,163,967,986]" captionTargetBox="[136,786,299,942]" captionTargetId="figure-610@3.[133,789,296,944]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 2. – Distribution map of Tragia liberica Jongkind (squares) also showing all other Tragia L. specimens (stars) from Liberia from the BR, K, P and WAG herbaria." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5683603" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5683603/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="252">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
), the new species is the only 
<taxonomicName id="53C74D5123764A32FDEDA9743F02E216" box="[545,612,1337,1360]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Tragia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="252" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="A6B3EAC023764A32FDEDA9743F02E216" box="[545,612,1337,1360]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="252">Tragia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<collectingCountry id="ECD0764223764A32FD4FA9753FABE216" box="[643,717,1336,1360]" name="Liberia" pageId="3" pageNumber="252">Liberia</collectingCountry>
that is found in the wet evergreen forest. The evergreen forest in 
<collectingCountry id="ECD0764223764A32FD04A9153E75E236" box="[712,787,1368,1392]" name="Liberia" pageId="3" pageNumber="252">Liberia</collectingCountry>
is mainly confined to a belt of variable width from north-west to south-east starting close to the ocean and changing to drier forest, like semi-deciduous forest, more inland (a reliable vegetation map of 
<collectingCountry id="ECD0764223764A32FE84A9953CF2E2B6" box="[328,404,1496,1520]" name="Liberia" pageId="3" pageNumber="252">Liberia</collectingCountry>
does not exist.) 
<taxonomicName id="53C74D5123764A32FDF0A9943FE6E2B6" box="[572,640,1497,1520]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Tragia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="252" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="A6B3EAC023764A32FDF0A9943FE6E2B6" box="[572,640,1497,1520]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="252">Tragia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
plants are not very conspicuous and are probably more common than can be concluded from this distribution map but the pattern is obvious even with this small number of specimens. The other specimens from 
<collectingCountry id="ECD0764223764A32FF0EAA153C68E136" box="[194,270,1624,1648]" name="Liberia" pageId="3" pageNumber="252">Liberia</collectingCountry>
are not all identified to species level but are all of species with a conspicuous cordate to narrowly cordate-acute leaf blade base, such as 
<taxonomicName id="53C74D5123764A32FE40AAD43E69E1F6" authority="Pax &amp; K. Hoffm." authorityName="Pax &amp; K. Hoffm." box="[396,783,1688,1712]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Tragia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="252" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="mildbraediana">
<emphasis id="A6B3EAC023764A32FE40AAD43F27E1F6" box="[396,577,1688,1712]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="252">T. mildbraediana</emphasis>
Pax &amp; K. Hoffm.
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="53C74D5123764A32FF44AAF43C33E196" authority="Benth." authorityName="Benth." box="[136,341,1720,1744]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Tragia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="252" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="spathulata">
<emphasis id="A6B3EAC023764A32FF44AAF43C61E196" box="[136,263,1720,1744]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="252">T. spathulata</emphasis>
Benth.
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="53C74D5123764A32FE47AAF43FE8E196" authority="Benth. These" authorityName="Benth. These" box="[395,654,1720,1744]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Tragia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="252" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tenuifolia">
<emphasis id="A6B3EAC023764A32FE47AAF43F67E196" box="[395,513,1720,1744]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="252">T. tenuifolia</emphasis>
Benth. These
</taxonomicName>
three 
<taxonomicName id="53C74D5123764A32FD02AAF43DD7E1B6" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Tragia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="252" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="A6B3EAC023764A32FD02AAF43E74E196" box="[718,786,1721,1744]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="252">Tragia</emphasis>
spp.
</taxonomicName>
are also known from the forest in 
<collectingCountry id="ECD0764223764A32FDC7AA953FF6E1B6" box="[523,656,1752,1776]" name="Sierra Leone" pageId="3" pageNumber="252">Sierra Leone</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="ECD0764223764A32FD55AA943E74E1B6" box="[665,786,1752,1777]" name="Ivory Coast" pageId="3" pageNumber="252">Ivory Coast</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="ECD0764223764A32FF7AAAB53D98E056" box="[182,254,1784,1808]" name="Ghana" pageId="3" pageNumber="252">Ghana</collectingCountry>
and grow there in forest with a lower rainfall than where 
<taxonomicName id="53C74D5123764A32FF01AB543C49E076" box="[205,303,1816,1840]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Tragia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="252" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="liberica">
<emphasis id="A6B3EAC023764A32FF01AB543C49E076" box="[205,303,1816,1840]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="252">T. liberica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is found.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
